<%# locals: (parcel:, assignable_orders_options: nil)
    The unmatched tab's row. Carries a dom_id so parcels#update's turbo_stream
    response can target it — without one, Turbo's replace/remove silently
    matched nothing and the assign form appeared to do nothing at all. Note the
    hidden `tab` field: it tells the controller which of the two row shapes to
    stream back.

    assignable_orders_options, when given, is a precomputed options HTML
    string embedded directly — used by the single-row turbo_stream replace,
    where rendering the full list once more is free. When omitted (the
    index page's many-row case), the row instead ships an empty <select>
    that a Stimulus controller populates from a <template> rendered once by
    the page — see app/javascript/controllers/lazy_options_controller.js for
    why: writing the full order list into every row's markup made page
    weight scale as rows × orders. %>
<tr id="<%= dom_id(parcel) %>">
  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900"><%= parcel.identifier %></td>
  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-500"><%= parcel.tracking_number %></td>
  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-500"><%= parcel.service_channel %></td>
  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-right text-gray-900"><%= number_to_currency(parcel.cost_amount) %></td>
  <td class="px-4 py-3">
    <% if current_membership&.owner? %>
      <%= form_with url: parcel_path(parcel), method: :patch, class: "flex gap-2" do %>
        <%= hidden_field_tag :tab, "unmatched" %>
        <% if assignable_orders_options %>
          <%= select_tag "parcel[order_id]", assignable_orders_options,
                include_blank: true,
                class: "rounded-md border-gray-300 text-sm" %>
        <% else %>
          <%= select_tag "parcel[order_id]", "",
                include_blank: true,
                class: "rounded-md border-gray-300 text-sm",
                data: { controller: "lazy-options",
                        lazy_options_template_value: "assignable-orders-options",
                        lazy_options_target: "select" } %>
        <% end %>
        <%= submit_tag t("parcels.assign"),
              class: "px-3 py-1 text-sm border border-gray-300 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-50 cursor-pointer" %>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>
  </td>
</tr>
